From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Toon Verwaest <verwaest@chromium.org>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 19:48:39 +0200
Subject: [maglev] Fix scope tracking at dead merge points in resumable
 functions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

MarkBytecodeDead failed to update current_scope_info_ from the merge state
at dead merge points in resumable functions. This lead to stale scope
information being used in subsequent dead bytecodes, which can cause
DCHECK failures when accessing context slots.

Fixed by synchronizing current_scope_info_ from the merge state (if
available) in MarkBytecodeDead.

TAG=agy

Bug: 501676158
Change-Id: I6500f7cedb0a8892d940b32883fdb164ac7a2eef
Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/v8/v8/+/7780217
Reviewed-by: Olivier Flückiger <olivf@chromium.org>
Commit-Queue: Olivier Flückiger <olivf@chromium.org>
Auto-Submit: Toon Verwaest <verwaest@chromium.org>
Cr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/main@{#106694}

diff --git a/src/maglev/maglev-graph-builder.cc b/src/maglev/maglev-graph-builder.cc
index b53c8ee7d8fc9947b2306a9610a31cba0f8b109b..ae8ed4e0c9550605d8362eb668fab78850c74602 100644
--- a/src/maglev/maglev-graph-builder.cc
+++ b/src/maglev/maglev-graph-builder.cc
@@ -17432,7 +17432,9 @@ void MaglevGraphBuilder::MarkBytecodeDead() {
   DCHECK_NULL(current_block());
   if (is_resumable_function_) {
     int current_offset = iterator_.current_offset();
-    if (merge_states_[current_offset] == nullptr) {
+    if (merge_states_[current_offset] != nullptr) {
+      SetCurrentScopeInfo(merge_states_[current_offset]->context_scope_info());
+    } else {
       auto it = dead_scope_infos_.find(current_offset);
       if (it != dead_scope_infos_.end()) {
         SetCurrentScopeInfo(it->second);
